                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic" corresp="#ms_i2">
                        <locus from="16v" to="25r"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <desc>Mediocre hand with small characters. The writing conveys an uneven
                           picture, because the space between the ruled lines varies and the writing
                           lines were not drawn straight (<locus target="#19r #24r"/>). <persName
                              ref="PRS13280WaldaAma" role="scribe">Walda ʾAmānuʾel</persName> is
                           mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#25r"/>.</desc></handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic" corresp="#ms_i3 #ms_i4">
                        <locus from="25v" to="40r"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1976">19th/20th century</date>
                        <desc>Rushed hand of a scribe named <persName ref="PRS13281HayMar"
                              role="scribe">Ḫāyla Māryām</persName> (<locus target="#35r"/>). Since
                           the handwriting becomes highly irregular with the beginning of the
                           incomplete <ref target="#ms_i4"/> (from <locus target="#35v"/> onward,
                           see esp. the change of appearance from <locus target="#38r"/> to <locus
                              target="#39v"/>), it seems quite possible that <ref target="#ms_i4"/>
                           was written by another, yet inexperienced scribe.</desc></handNote>

